00:15:21,415 --> 00:15:22,856
all these things can be exclusionary.

280
00:15:24,077 --> 00:15:27,419
And some of the barriers that VR throws up

281
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:29,521
are kind of inherent to the platform.

282
00:15:30,061 --> 00:15:31,902
There's not much you can do about them, but a lot of them

283
00:15:32,343 --> 00:15:34,264
can actually be addressed through just good accessible

284
00:15:34,304 --> 00:15:34,564
design.

285
00:15:38,285 --> 00:15:43,409
Which people are realizing, there's a lot of developers who are really, really passionate

286
00:15:43,449 --> 00:15:47,512
about accessibility in VR, and they're doing some really, really nice things, really nice

287
00:15:47,572 --> 00:15:49,434
creative approaches to accessibility in VR.

288
00:15:51,332 --> 00:15:53,053
And this is really, really exciting for me to see,

289
00:15:53,113 --> 00:15:55,715
because we haven't had this before with a new platform.

